OL,3,CMuriel McKay's son to come face-to-
OL,4,Cface with mother's killer in bid to
OL,5,Cfind body
OL,7,F"We need to get information from
OL,8,FNizamodeen. My sister Diane embraced
OL,9,Fhim at the time when they first met
OL,10,Fhim in Trinidad.
OL,12,F"I wasn't surprised. I think a lot of
OL,13,Fpeople were surprised. But the problem
OL,14,Fis we have to get this information and
OL,15,Fit's only by getting his confidence
OL,16,Fand his cooperation which we worked
OL,17,Fvery hard to build up.
OL,19,F"And he made a confession. He
OL,20,Fconfessed to the fact that he had
OL,21,Fburied her."
